### English Title:
Chinese Suppliers Flood US Social Media, Encouraging Direct Purchases to Bypass Tariffs

### English Text Summary:
Chinese suppliers have inundated American social media, urging users to bypass the 145% tariffs imposed by President Trump on Beijing by purchasing directly from their factories. A TikTok user claimed to manufacture original goods for luxury brands, showcasing expensive handbags. Despite the allure, experts doubt the legitimacy of these claims, emphasizing that genuine manufacturers typically sign non-disclosure agreements. The article highlights the reliance of American consumers on Chinese products and the implications of tariffs on access to preferred goods. It also discusses the environmental impact of consumerism and the potential consequences of relying on Chinese supply chains.

